# Version Symbol Migration

`src/version.h` defines `SHEKYL_*` as the canonical version symbols and
provides `MONERO_*` macro aliases for backward compatibility during the
Monero upstream merge window.

## Rule

When editing any C/C++ file under `src/` that references `MONERO_VERSION`,
`MONERO_VERSION_TAG`, `MONERO_RELEASE_NAME`, `MONERO_VERSION_FULL`, or
`MONERO_VERSION_IS_RELEASE`:

1. Replace those references with the corresponding `SHEKYL_*` symbol.
2. Do **not** perform a repo-wide rename — only migrate symbols in the file
   you are already modifying for other work.
3. Do **not** touch `src/version.h` macro aliases; they exist intentionally
   so un-migrated files and upstream cherry-picks keep compiling.

## Lifecycle

- These aliases will be removed in a single cleanup PR after the V4
  lattice-only hard fork stabilizes and Monero upstream merges are no longer
  expected.
- At that point, any remaining `MONERO_*` references will be swept and
  replaced in bulk.
